UNIVERSITY OF NORTH ALABAMAADJUNCT INSTRUCTORS(Part Time) The University of North Alabama invites applications for adjunct (part-time) instructors for the 2022 summer term and fall semester. Persons holding adjunct teaching positions normally teach three to six credit hours or nine contact hours per semester.

Adjunct teaching positions will be available in a number of departments but greatest needs are anticipated in the following areas: accounting, business law, chemistry, cinematic arts &amp;
theatre, computer information systems, computer science, data analytics, economics, engineering &amp;
technology, earth science, English, finance, foreign languages (Spanish), geography, history (history &amp;
religious studies), interdisciplinary &amp;
professional studies, management, marketing, mathematics, music, occupational health science, physics, psychology, social work, and sociology.

Minimum qualifications require adjunct instructors to hold a masters degree plus a minimum of 18 graduate semester hours in the desired teaching discipline.

Payment for adjunct teaching is on a standardized university scale according to credit or contact hours taught. For detailed information on these postings and to apply, please visit our Online Employment System at http://jobs.

una.edu. Applications will only be accepted through this system. For questions, please email employment@una.edu or call 256.765.4291 and select option #2. Selecting an option other than #2 will result in a delayed response.

UNA is an equal opportunity employer committed to achieving excellence and strength through diversity. UNA seeks a wide range of applicants for these positions so that one of our core values, ethnic and cultural diversity, will be affirmed. UNA is a smoke-free campus.
